<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id8ee09e04-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s290h–1"><num value="290h–1">§ 290h–1.</num><heading> United States African Development Foundation</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id8ee09e05-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s290h–1/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Establishment of Foundation</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There is established a body corporate to be known as the “United States African Development Foundation” (hereafter in this subchapter referred to as the “Foundation”).</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id8ee09e06-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s290h–1/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Principal and branch offices</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Foundation shall establish a principal office in the United States and may establish such branch offices in Africa as may be necessary to carry out its functions.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id8ee09e07-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">(<ref href="/us/pl/96/533/tV/s503">Pub. L. 96–533, title V, § 503</ref>, <date date="1980-12-16">Dec. 16, 1980</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/94/3152">94 Stat. 3152</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/113/76/dK/tIII">Pub. L. 113–76, div. K, title III</ref>, <date date="2014-01-17">Jan. 17, 2014</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/128/482">128 Stat. 482</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
